<define-tag description>security update</define-tag>
<define-tag moreinfo>
<p>Several vulnerabilities were discovered in wordpress, a web blogging
tool. They would allow remote attackers to force password resets, and
perform various cross-site scripting and cross-site request forgery
attacks.</p>

<p>For the stable distribution (jessie), these problems have been fixed in
version 4.1+dfsg-1+deb8u13.</p>

<p>For the upcoming stable (stretch) and unstable (sid) distributions,
these problems have been fixed in version 4.7.5+dfsg-1.</p>

<p>We recommend that you upgrade your wordpress packages.</p>
</define-tag>

